Step 1: Create EC2 Instance
Step 2: Select Ubuntu AMI
Step 3: Create .pem key
Step 4: Allow SSH, HTTPS and HTTP then Launch Instance
Step 5: Open Ubantu
Step 6: Go to the .pem key path
Step 7: Copy SSH link from Instance and Paste
Step 8: sudo su -
Step 9: apt-get update
Step 10: apt-get install nginx -y
Step 11: service nginx status
Step 12: curl localhost
Step 13: Open browser and paste Instance public ip nginx page will display.
